        <prompt>What was the primary goal of the American Protective League during WWI?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To protect the president</option>
            <option letter="b">To spy on fellow citizens</option>
            <option letter="c">To distribute war bonds</option>
            <option letter="d">To train soldiers</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The American Protective League was a volunteer organization that worked with the Justice Department to spy on and report fellow citizens suspected of being "un-American" or disloyal during WWI.</explanation>
