    <question>
        <prompt>How did Wilson's stroke affect his presidency?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">He recovered quickly</option>
            <option letter="b">His wife secretly managed affairs</option>
            <option letter="c">He resigned immediately</option>
            <option letter="d">Congress took control</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>After Wilson's severe stroke in 1919, his wife Edith effectively managed many presidential duties, keeping his condition secret from the public and making many decisions herself.</explanation>
